[div class=p 
	"Punch-Out!! No TKO is a hack of Mike Tyson's Punch-Out!! It has the same opponents, same patterns, very different strategies, since you can't TKO your opponents. However, you have infinite star punches, allowing for ultra-fast knockdowns.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Glass Joe: It's faster (in-game time) to knock him down several times, rather than knock him out at 42.00, as shown here.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Von Kaiser: Since we have infinite star punches, you don't have to get a star; just duck, jab, star for knockdown 1. When he gets up, duck his punch, and star him. Same for phase 3, which will KO him.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Piston Honda 1: I can't find the pattern for 36.97 TKO on my own, had to use 40.25 strat for phase 1 and a modified strat for phase 3.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Don Flamenco 1: Just do the same strat, except don't get a star at the beginning.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"King Hippo: Oh boy, this fight was hard to optimize. Landing a star into his open-mouth punches deals more damage than normal, so I do that where needed.
	$LF
	"Great Tiger: Five star punches will knock him down for the first time. He gets up on 1 twice, so two more stars send him down twice more. I throw 1 more star punch, which he takes, but then he'd start dodging my star punches if I didn't jab, block or dodge, jab (if blocked) and star (either way.) I do this twice in total for this phase. For the next phase, punch, dodge, star, repeat, jab, block, jab, star for the knockdown. When he gets up, punch, dodge, star. Now he goes into punches on his own, a lot faster. Duck his punch, jab, star for the knockdown. Duck, star for KO.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Bald Bull 1: Uses 52.82 strat for phases 1, 2 and 3. For phases 4 and 5, I do 55.25 strat, since I don't have 3 stars anymore. For phase 6, throw 3 stars to counter all three of his hooks, dodge his uppercut and throw a star punch. He will get up on the count of 1, so counter his punch with a star punch to send him down again. Here's where he gets up on the count of 9, like Bald Bull 2. Duck his first three punches, following up with a star punch after each one. Dodge his uppercut, and press Start, which will send him down to the mat again. Now, the Bull Charge will happen, since the clock is at the right time to do so. Hit him in the gut at the right time, and send him down in one hit. When he gets up, counter two hooks with two star punches, wait for the rolling jabs, and star him for the knockdown. Star him twice more for the KO!
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Piston Honda 2: This is the one fight that uses only star punches to knock out the opponent.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Soda Popinski: This fight takes advantage of his instant knockdown. Since you only have 8 hearts, some more star punches had to be used.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Bald Bull 2: Uses 1:08.48 strat to start, then uses only star punches. This was a pain in the butt to optimize.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Don Flamenco 2: My goal was to try to get him down in just one cycle each time.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Sandman: Uses all the stars at the beginning, dodging and countering with gut punches where needed. When he goes into the hooks pattern, I duck and throw star punches where faster, or punch, dodge, jab, star punch where faster.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Super Macho Man: Uses normal fastest no CS strat for phases 1, 2 and 3. After that, the fight continues from there.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Mike Tyson: Mike has an interesting property: if you throw a gut punch after he throws an uppercut, then do a misdirected gut punch, then throw a star punch, Mike will always take the star punch. This is used to our advantage heavily here. As a side note, the TAS ends on the final star punch; I intentionally let him do 2 fake get-ups since I can't do it anywhere else without losing time.
	$LF
	"Other comments:
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Oh boy, this was painful to optimize at times, but overall, so much fun. It is possible to KO everyone except Great Tiger and Bald Bull in the original game, but this hack is a way to KO everyone. Happy April Fools day!
	$LF
]div
