[div class=p 
	[a class=intlink href=/Users/Profile/Samsara 
		"Samsara
	]a
	": Normally ROM hacks are judged based on audience feedback, but I think it's pretty safe to judge this one right here. The hack is ultimately redundant, it removes TKOs and for some reason makes up for it by giving unlimited star punches, which I feel really takes away from the point of not being able to TKO. As 
	(__wikiLink|displaytext=adelikat said in this post|href=/Forum/Posts/504466)
	", removing the TKOs without adding unlimited stars would lead to more interesting strats while still being completely possible to do, and I believe "removing the TKOs" could be done in the original game by not going for them on any of the opponents. Feel free to correct me on this, I'm not that familiar with Punch-Out so I don't know for sure if it can be done without hacking, but if so, that would definitely be the preferred way of doing this run, and if not, then a version of the hack that doesn't add unlimited star punches would be the preferred one here.
	$LF
]div
[div class=p 
	"Rejecting for hack choice, but I do feel like a "no TKO" branch is still worth investigating, so don't be discouraged.
]div
